# Testing discipline

Two layers. Both run locally with `npm test` and in CI on every push / PR.
Neither is allowed to go red on main.

## Layer 1 ŌĆö `scripts/check-structure.mjs` (static)

- No browser, no network. Reads files off disk and greps.
- Catches the boring-but-deadly regressions:
  - a required file was deleted,
  - a required module stopped being imported by `main.js`,
  - section order was silently shuffled,
  - `demo-viewer.js` stopped delegating to the three sub-modules,
  - a required CSS shard / vendor JS went missing,
  - a required `package.json` script was removed,
  - core infrastructure (`src/config/index.js`, `src/core/*.js`) is gone.
- Rule: if you introduce a new **structural** invariant (a new phase, a
  new required file, a new canonical ordering), add a `must(...)` line.
- Keep `must()` labels human-readable ŌĆö they appear verbatim in CI logs.
- Comment stripping is already in place for `main.js` / `demo-viewer.js`
  import detection; use the same `strippedX` pattern when extending.

## Layer 2 ŌĆö `scripts/smoke.mjs` (Puppeteer)

- Runs the **built** site through `vite preview`, drives a headless
  Chrome, asserts **observable user behavior**.
- Every new user-visible feature earns at least one `assert(...)` /
  `assertEq(...)` / `assertGte(...)` here.
- Keep these invariants stable ŌĆö they are the core contract:
  - 9 sections present in the DOM
  - 6 vendors (`jquery`, `wow`, `parallax`, `morphext`, `counterup`, `waypoint`)
    reach the global scope
  - Projects section renders exactly 12 demo cards
  - Works section renders Ōēź 7 grid items on page 1
  - `?code=990718` reveals the experience section
  - Scrolling to `#works` triggers the isotope + magnific-popup lazy load
  - Clicking a demo card opens the full-screen viewer with a title
  - Theme toggle: lightŌåÆdark leaves 0 `.light` nodes; darkŌåÆlight restores Ōēź 50
  - Preloader fades to hidden
  - **0 pageerrors, 0 console.error, 0 failed same-origin requests**
- Third-party hosts (`botpress`, `bpcontent.cloud`, `formspree`) are
  excluded from the failed-request assertion via `isThirdParty()` ŌĆö
  keep that list accurate; don't silence same-origin failures.

## Writing smoke assertions well

- Prefer `assertEq(count, expected, label)` over `assert(count > 0, ...)`
  for render-count invariants ŌĆö drift is easier to diagnose.
- Always give every assert a **label** that answers "what broke?" when
  you read it alone in a CI log line. Avoid labels like `ok`, `check`.
- Sleep sparingly; prefer `page.waitForFunction(ŌĆ”)` for anything that
  isn't a known animation/debounce delay.

## `npm test` wiring (`scripts/run-smoke.mjs`)

- Builds if `dist/` is missing, then spawns `vite preview`, polls the
  port, runs `smoke.mjs`, and cleans up on any exit path.
- If you change the preview port, respect the `SMOKE_PORT` / `SMOKE_URL`
  env vars; don't hard-code.
- Keep the script process-signal-safe ŌĆö it must kill the preview on
  SIGINT/SIGTERM, or CI leaks processes.

## Local quick commands

```bash
npm run test:static   # fastest, run this first during iterative edits
npm run build         # sanity check bundler output
npm run test:smoke    # full E2E; ~12s locally
npm test              # both, same as CI
```
